PHONE_REDACTEDT09:PORT:PORT.841163Z	   31 Query	insert into daily_analysis_reports (analysis_confidence,analysis_scope_note,day,executive_summary,generated_at,misconfiguration_signals,system_behavior_analysis,user_behavior_analysis) values ('High confidence due to the consistency in the failure breakdown, user activity patterns, and temporal behavior data.','This analysis is based on the provided data from a single calendar day (IST) focusing on backend lead submission behavior.','PHONE_REDACTED','On the PHONE_REDACTED, a total of 187 lead submission attempts were made, resulting in 137 successful submissions and 50 failures. EMAIL_REDACTED accounted for 54.9% of the total attempts and 73.9% of the failures. Duplicate leads were the primary cause of failure, with 48 instances, and there were no rate limit exceeded cases at any final page.','PHONE_REDACTED:PORT:PORT.832999','The high frequency of duplicate lead submissions and the absence of rate limit exceeded cases at final pages might indicate a misconfiguration in the system or an integration issue that allows for multiple submission attempts of the same lead.','The system handled up to 17 attempts per minute and did not exhibit any burst activity patterns throughout the day. The rate limit exceeded cases were minimal, but none occurred at final pages, which may suggest a configuration issue or inconsistency with the defined rate limit thresholds.','EMAIL_REDACTED had a higher submission volume and a higher failure ratio compared to EMAIL_REDACTED. The discrepancy suggests that EMAIL_REDACTED may have encountered more duplicate lead submissions than EMAIL_REDACTED, which could potentially be addressed through improved handling or monitoring.')
