PHONE_REDACTEDT09:PORT:PORT.434409Z	   30 Query	insert into daily_analysis_reports (analysis_confidence,analysis_scope_note,day,executive_summary,generated_at,misconfiguration_signals,system_behavior_analysis,user_behavior_analysis) values ('The analysis is based on the provided data and suggests a high level of confidence in the observations, particularly regarding user behavior and system volume.','This analysis covers a single day (PHONE_REDACTED) and focuses solely on backend lead submission behavior.','PHONE_REDACTED','On the analyzed day (PHONE_REDACTED), a total of 187 backend lead submissions were made, with 137 successful and 50 failed submissions. The success ratio was 73.26%. User behavior shows high activity from EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED, accounting for 186 attempts out of the total. Duplicate leads constituted a significant portion of the failures, with 48 instances.','PHONE_REDACTED:PORT:PORT.426432','The high number of duplicate leads (48) could suggest potential configuration or integration issues with the lead submission system.','The system demonstrated no signs of rate limiting based on the provided data, as only two instances of RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED errors occurred and no such failures were associated with a final page. The peak attempt rate was 17 submissions per minute, with no burst minutes.','EMAIL_REDACTED showed a higher failure ratio at 36.63%, while EMAIL_REDACTED had a lower failure ratio of 15.29%. The majority (100%) of attempts were made through the website form.')
